inn1.comm: in the channel outside off and Watson shoulders arms. No four, no six just a dot ball. What has the world come to?
extra bounce on this, around the off stump line, Watson leans forward to defend and it makes contact with the top of the bat and runs to point
In business. here we go. Short poor delivery outside off and Watto drag-pulls it through midwicket.
wide outside the off stump, Watson goes for it but can't connect. Umpire Cloete doesn't call it a wide
Blasted. He stand and admires. He now moves down the track to do some gardening. It was imperious shot. He went on the front foot, reached out and crashed it through covers. Another shortish delivery
Last game he hit everything through leg and Bangladesh are now correcting it by bowling too much outside off. Watson forces this one as well but Mahmudullah makes a diving save at point
In the channel outside off and Ponting does what he does: That forward lunge and he shoulders arms
it was the short delivery on the off stump and Ricky swivels to pull it to deep square-leg boundary. Crunched!
gets forward, covers the off stump and shoulders arms.

dropped by Razzak at midwicket. It was a shortish delivery around of and Ponting goes for the pull and Razzak dives forward but couldn't hold on. It was dying on him. Cue: costly miss and all that jazz
pushes this to the leg side region for a single
That front-foot chop down to third man. Typical Watto shot. One run and he retains the strike

Only Brian Close would have called this a Drop catch. Watson smashed this on the up and on the front foot and the bowler put his left hand out but it brushed his finger tips and rushed to the straight boundary
He reached forward and heaved this slower one to long-on boundary. he didn't quite connect it as well as he would have liked but picks up a boundary nevertheless
hattrick of fours. This is the best of the lot. No violence this time. he waited on the front foot, opened the bat-face and chopped it past backward point
in the zone outside off stump, Watson tries to run it down to third man but doesn't connect
wide outside off stump, Watson mistimes the cut to cover
More violence. Where is the referee? He thrust his front foot and drilled this past Punter. Whack
gets back to defend this to the off side
gets back to work this to midwicket. Ponting goes for a stroll to the leg side
Another poor delivery. Short and down the leg side and Ricky helps it along to the long-leg boundary. He then just has a look at the track. yep, lovely batting pitch this Punter!
What a lovely lovely shot. Classy. It was a length delivery outside off stump, Ponting glided across to punch it so sweetly on the up and through covers.
full in length, Ponting eases this to point
That imperious Ponting pull. He makes it look so easy. He swivelled as soon as he saw the short length and pulled it gracefully over midwicket boundary.
flicks this past square-leg for a single
Oh well its another four. It was a length delivery outside off, Ponting waited and cut it late to left of backward point
dot ball. Gold! Ponting gets back to defend this to the on side
stretches forward and across to drive neatly to right of short extra cover
tries the slower bouncer. Watto whack-pulls it to the right of backward square-leg fielder (Razzak) who should have made better effort to stop it
gets forward to on drive it past mid-on for a single
Ah! the carnage continues. I am dreading that I am going to run out of adjectives here. This is a shortish delivery on the pads and Watson glances it down to fine-leg
full in length and straightening on the off and middle, squeezed out to backward point
wide outside off, Watson chases it but doesn't reach
fetches this from outside off stump, dragged down to long-on
wide outside off, on the tramlines, Ponting reaches out to mistime it to cover
gets forward to ease it to left of mid-on
Thunderous wallop! Watson gets forward and kills this full delivery to the long-off boundary. One bounce and four.
leans forward to squeeze this to point
leans forward to drive it back down the track and the bowler makes a half-stop
slower cutter, worked away to deep midwicket
leans well forward to steer this length delivery to backward point
cuts in towards the middle, from short of length, pushed to mid-on; they think about a single but kill the thought
full in length, on the middle, eased to mid-on
goes hard into this drive and ends up dragging this full delivery from around off stump to long-on
slower, well outside off, Ponting goes back and across to cut it to cover point
Ponting walked down the track and shoved the slower cutter over midwicket for a nonchalant boundary
threatens to jump out before he stays at the crease and works it past square-leg
Murderous blow! He cleared the front foot and crashed the length delivery over long-on
beaten by the slower one. he is through early into the heave and the ball arrives later and wobbles over the middle stump
comes on slowly off the track and Ponting checks his push to the leg side
turns this past square-leg for a single

Not many in the crowd today but Watson is keeping the scarce turnout wary of being attacked with the ball. This one flies into the midwicket stands. He backed away and pulled this no ball over the boundary
gets back to turn this to short fine-leg
quicker one, on the middle and Watson just about manages to stab it off the inside edge clear of the leg stump.
This time he rocks back to cut it hard to the point boundary. Who can stop this man?
retains the strike with a on drive
slower in the air, full in length, Watson misses the drive and edges it to his pad
floated full outside leg, Watson goes for a big swing over square-leg, misses and it rolls off the pad
Much fun. Watson gets down on his knee and drags this to the cowcorner- between deep midwicket and long-on
push-drives this to long-on for a single
works this past square-leg for a single
The slog-sweeping orgy continues. This one has been picked up at deep midwicket.
well outside the off stump, Watson was gunning for the big hit but checks his shot and reaches out to swat it away
again well outside the off- this is the plan to Watto-  pushed to the off
Yep, that's the plan allright. This one is also well outside off and Watson reaches out and drags it to sweeper cover
closer to the off and Ricky punches it to sweeper cover
closer to the off stump this time, full in length and Watson gets greedy and goes for a big swing to the long-on region but edges it to short fine-leg
Absolutely thumped! Six on the off side. They kept bowling there at him and this time Watson got close to the ball and whacked it over long-off. Flat-batted thump
gets forward to deflect this to midwicket
leans forward to defend it back to the bowler
wide down the leg side, Ponting fails to connect with the sweep
nudged to the on side, Watson wants the single but is sent back
gets back to force this one down to sweeper cover

Watson is out. Will the entertainment end? The crowd roar in delight. It was a nice delivery, much slower through the air and Watson is beaten by the lack of pace. he went for the big slog sweep and missed it completely. The ball landed, winked at him and gently pegged back the off stump.
fuller, on the leg side, Clarke glances it down to fine-leg boundary
leans forward to work this to midwicket
stretches well forward to defend this down the track
leans forward to deflect it to midwicket
moves well outside leg and lifts this delivery over extra cover. The bowler had followed him but Ponting got well outside and went inside-out
slower, outside leg, Ponting sweeps it to fine-leg region
leans forward and across to defend and it runs off the edge to the leg side
gets well back to punch this to long-off
on the off stump line, carefully dabbed to cover
opts for the sweep this time and sweeps well to pick up a boundary to backward-square leg boundary
plays the paddle sweep this time and will collect two runs
quicker on the middle, Ponting backs away to push it to cover
leans forward to defend this to the on side
gets back to work this behind square-leg
on the leg stump line, lapped around the corner to short fine-leg
leans forward to defend to the off side
rushes down the track to defend to the leg side
on the middle stump line, worked to midwicket
gets forward to defend to the midwicket fielder. Tight over
gets back to punch it out to deep cover
leans well forward to defend

Ponting is not happy but he has to go. It was the full delivery on the middle and Ponting went for the sweep and missed it completely. that looked pretty close unless of course the ball was turning away sharply.
tossed up on off, defended down the track
again full and speared in, now that Watson is gone he is giving it some air. Smith defends.
Smith advances, Razzak sees him and drifts it onto leg stump, Smith covers the line and flicks to midwicket
loopy ball on leg stump, Clarke advances and plays it down the ground
length ball, straightens from outside off and Clarke pushes it off the back foot
on the pads, Clarke skips inside the line and flicks to midwicket. The run rate is beginning to look more believable now.
again pushed back of a length and Clarke pushes into the covers.
Clarke jumps out, gets to the flight and flicks but can't beat midwicket. I'll eat my hat if this is a maiden.
my hat survives. Clarke comes out and drives through extra cover for a single.
uses his feet ,reaches the pitch of the ball and lofts it to wide long-on
drives to the off side for a single
skips down the track and drives to long-off
quickish arm ball , pushed back to the bowler
rocks back to punch it to sweeper cover
goes down the track and drags it to right of midwicket where a diving stop is made
gets back to deflect it to midwicket
moves down the track and works it past square-leg for a single
slower, fuller, on the off stump, pushes it out to the off
gets down the track and whips it to wide long-on boundary. Whippy!
jabs this to midwicket. high back lift

Caught and bowled! He took two steps down the track and ended up chipping it back to the bowler. Greg Mathews murmurs on air, "What a wasted opportunity" Tame dismissal but the bowler has to be given credit for getting the ball to dip
low full toss on the pads, flicked away to deep midwicket
this one straightens on the middle, jabbed out to the off
stays back to push this back to the bowler
slider outside off, punched out to deep point
drags this one really short and Clarke pulls this to deep midwicket
shortish delivery, pulled away for a single
floated full outside off, driven to right of mid-off
goes down the track and on drives to long-on
leans well forward to steer this through cover point
gets back to clip this behind square-leg
drifts to the pads and Hussey glances it to fine-leg region.
leans forward to defend to the off side
gets forward to drive it back to the bowler
low full toss, whipped away to deep midwicket
Googly! Hussey cuts this to sweeper cover
backs away to punch it to sweeper cover
leans forward to on drive it to long-on
another googly, fuller this time, dabbed to backward point
Lovely shot. He rushed down the track and caressed an off drive through wide mid-off region
flighted on the middle, on driven to long-on
on the middle stump line, dabbed to square-leg
well outside the off stump, cut away to point
skips down the track and flicks it away to fine-leg region. Mortaza makes a fine diving save there. He lunged forward and back-flicked the ball back into play
on the off stump line, defended to the bowler
push-drives this to long-on
gets back to push this back to the bowler
slower, bit more air, fuller, flicked past square-leg for a single
stays round the stumps for the righty as well, clipped to deep midwicket
not all that short but Hussey rocks back to cut to sweeper cover
moves down the track and pushes it back to the bowler
plays the reverse sweep and gets the placement superbly. it was a reverse paddle and he hit it well to the right of short third man
tickles this to right of short third man again - not a reverse sweep, he steered this one- fielded
sashays down the track and off drives to long-off
flighted full outside, on driven to long-on
from round the stumps, around off, punched to Shakib at short extra cover
slower, flighted, fuller, and Clarke gets into his comfort zone - down the track and drives it to long-on
on driven again for yet another single
leans forward to dab this to short midwicket
stretches forward to push this wide of cover for a single
stays back to punch it to long-off for a single
goes down the track and pushes it back to the bowler
slightly short in length, cut to backward point
stays well back to punch this to long-off for a single
on the middle and off line, turned to midwicket
on the pads, turned to square-leg
floated on the leg stump line, swept away to the square-leg boundary
rotates the strike with an on drive to long-on
slower, turning away, cut to extra cover
works this through wide midwicket for a single
gets forward to work it to midwicket
retreats further back inside the crease, pulled away to deep midwicket
gets forward to push this back to the offie
turns away from the off stump, Hussey works it away to sweeper cover
moves down the track, doesn't reach the pitch of the ball and blocks it towards midwicket
yet another single down to long-on. Milkmen at work here
And now through covers. risk-free
gets back to steer this to sweeper cover.
The singles keep coming. This one has been milked through to deep cover
Cut away to deep point. One more. Easy as easy gets.
Dot ball. Punched straight to short extra cover
Another cut. Another single. Australia skip along
on the pads, flicked away to deep midwicket
moves down the track and drives to long-off
slightly short and Clarke pulls it away to deep square-leg for a single
drifts in on the off and middle, full, driven to cover
opens his stance to drag the short ball to deep midwicket
works this to fine-leg region for a single
gets well back to cut this to right of sweeper cover
leans well forward to drive it to long-off
moves down the track, doesn't get to the pitch of the ball and lunges forward to defend
Shakib errs on length this time. Too full and Hussey unfurls the sweep shot. Powerful.
pulls this to deep midwicket for a single
gets back to cut this one for a single
tries to punch this to the off side but the slowness of the ball meant he edged it to the on side
on driven to the right of Mahmudullah who makes a diving stop
slips in a wide down the leg side
pulls but Shakib dives to his right at square-leg. Fine stop
nudges this towards Shakib for a quick single.
tossed up full, driven down to long-on
slowish turn back into Hussey who taps it towards Clarke
leans forward to drive this wide of midwicket for a single
moves down the track and edges it to the bowler
slips this to the leg side, worked away through backward square-leg region
slightly slow, stops on Clarke who reaches out, adjusts to the lack of pace and cuts to sweeper cover
Hussey pulls but Mortaza is there at deep midwicket.
turns from the off stump line, pushed to cover
fuller, just outside off and hussey square drives for a single
slower off break from round the stumps, defended on the front foot
gets back to clip this to deep midwicket for a single
on the off stump line, chopped away back down the track
50 up for Hussey. Run a ball. This one was short and Hussey wallops it over midwicket.

run out missred goes for the pull but misses. The ball turns to hit the thigh and runs to backward point region. Hussey calls Clarke for a single and they rush across to make it just in time to beat the throw at the non striker's end. Razzak didn't collect the throw cleanly and broke the stumps with bare hands.
leans forward to push this to the off
reverse sweeps this but straight to short third man
Crashes this to deep square-leg boundary with a powerful sweep shot. It was outside the leg stump line
slower, flighted, just outside off, squeezed past backward point
gets well  back to punch this to long-on for a single
full delivery, the slow yorker, outside off, Clarke lets it go
moves outside leg and heaves this through mid-on. he doesn't time it well and that allows them to come back for the second
fullish, hint of inswing and it beats Clarke's attempt to flick and raps the pad. going down leg, though

Clatter! Mortaza has knocked out the off stump. The Batting Powerplay strikes. It was the full delivery,  just short of the blockhole, on the off stump line, Clarke shuffled across and went for the big across-the-line swing. Mistake. No wood on leather but the opposite.
full in length, on the middle, defended to the on side

Shout for lbw. Mortaza thinks its pad first. VB Chandrasekhar, on air, thinks its close. Let's see on the replay. it was the full delivery on the off stump line and Ferguson was very late in getting forward to defend. Was it pad first? Or bat first? Replays please
moves in to the off stump line, Ferguson plays it very late and pushes it to extra cover. They rush for the single. Direct hit at the non striker's end but he is home
overpitched on the legs, flicked away for a single
pushed away to extra cover for a single
low full toss on the boot, flicked away for a single
driven to mid-off where Nafees makes a diving half-stop to his left
goes for the yorker, misses the blockhole, flicked away to deep midwicket
slower one, fullish, eased to long-off for a single
Another one goes down in the batting Powerplay and wicket no 150 for Mortaza Congrats sir. It was the full delivery and it was hit straight to mid-off. Fergy has combusted.
in the zone outside off, angling away and Mitch is beaten, poking at it
lovely delivery, cutting away from Mitch, who is beaten again.
beaten by the slower one this time. Supah over so far. Mitch was too early into his big shot and the ball gently wobbled past him
on the middle stump, full in length, looking for the lbw, mitch dabs it to right of cover
Smashed to the straight boundary. Mitch brought the bat down in a hurry and knifed through the line.
shortish ball outside off, Mitch is very eager to pull but goes too hard at it and misses. Hussey walks over for a chat
fuller, outside off, dragged down to long-on
very full, straight, eased to long-off for a single
backs away but mistimes this towards mid-off. He made contact with the toe end of the bat and Mitch inspects the damage.
shortish, pulled away for a single
slower cutter angling away from Hussey who dabs it to backward point for a single
leans forward to scoop this short of extra cover. Mushfiqur holds his head. It almost carried to the fielder
another slower one outside off, nudged to short third man region
Big swing and he connects. It was the full delivery on the off stump line and Mitch swings it to the midwicket boundary.
Crunchy. Meaty. Yummy! Mitch backed away to the leg side and crashed this full delivery over long-off.

And again. He has hammered this one. He moved outside leg and Mortaza, who had bowled couple of very good overs in this spell, again offers a full-pitched hit-me delivery. Mitch has crashed it over long-off
reaches outside off and cuts the short-of-length delivery wide of sweeper cover
Supah pull! Stylish and effective. He swivelled off the front foot and unfurled a nonchalant pull shot over square-leg boundary.
fullish delivery on the middle, driven to long-off
full and well outside off and Mitch reaches out to squeeze it - edged away- to third man boundary
slower cutter, outside off, dragged down to long-on
flicked away for a single
gets back to clip this through midwicket
slow off break from round the stumps, pushed out to cover
slightly slower, full in length, forced away to deep cover
turns away from the off, dabbed to backward point
slightly short in length, dragged down to long-on. Mitch isn't happy; he knows he should have pulled it wider
slips a wide down the leg side
drifts in towards middle, on driven to long-on
fullish delivery, almost an yorker, dug out back to the bowler
gets forward to straight drive past the bowler for a single
low full toss outside off and Mitch as ever doesn't lean fully  into his forward drives and again makes contact with the bottom of the bat
on the pads, rolls away for a leg bye
full and straight, driven straight to long-on. Just a single.
full pitched well outside off, sliced out to sweeper cover

Inside edge! It kept a touch low outside off and Mitch doesn't quite get into a good position to cut. His weight was falling back as he tried to reach out wit ha cut. Profitable inside edge takes it to fine-leg boundary, thoug
fetches it from outside off and drills it to long-on
turns away from the off stump, stabbed to backward point
well outside off, turning away, cut away to left of sweeper cover
gets forward and drives straight to cover
presses back to cut to deep cover region
Boshed!  He went down on his knee and swung this low full toss over midwicket.
yorker length outside off and Hussey can't get bat to ball
drives this to long-off for a single
Holes out to deep midwicket. Mitch show is over. It was a length delivery on the middle and Mitchell Johnson slogged it straight to deep midwicket.
leans forward to drive to long-off
leans forward to on drive this for a single
gets back to clip this to deep midwicket
rushes down the track and drives to long-on
turns in to middle stump line, pushed down to long-on
gets back to cut this to sweeper cover for single
spins in, moves past the attempted leg-side whip and hits the pad. It was missing the leg stump.
gets forward to on drive to long-on
paddles it around the corner for couple of runs
short and wide, cut away to sweeper cover
plays the sweep shot to rotate the strike
loud cry for lbw and the ump has raised the finger. He went for a reverse sweep but missed.
gets back to defend to the on side
around that off stump line, pushed out to cover
rushes down the track, gets outside leg and lifts this inside-out over extra cover. Fab strike.
And again. he sashayed down the track, got outside leg and crashed this over extra cover. Dropped by Shakib at extra cover. He got his hands up but it burst through the fingers.
works this to the leg side for a single
punched out to long-on for a single.
2006. 2007. 2011. This is the third hundred for Mike Hussey. He punched it through to the deep cover region. A very fine innings and his mates in the dressing room show their appreciation
Greg Mathews called John Hastings as "Monster from New South Wales" And he has absolutely smashed this to the straight boundary.
worked this behind square-leg for couple of runs
pushes it to midwicket and get across for the quick run. Had there been a direct hit at the non striker's end, he would have been a goner
goes for the big slog sweep but doesn't connect properly
Neat! He skipped down the track and creamed this to wide long-off boundary
dabs this to the on side for a single
Monstrous hit! He went down the track and has killed it. The white ball sails high over long-on boundary.
Looked pretty plumb. Full, straight, and on the middle. Hussey went for the paddle sweep but missed. Super-cool knock this. His third ton.
driven down to long-off for a single
full delivery, driven to the off side for a single
nice slower one, stabbed down the track and Shafiul should have had a run out. The non striker had backed up too far but shafiul failed to stop the ball.
full toss and that has been dealt with violence. A fierce square drive.
Hastings finishes things off in some style. Another full delivery and Hastings square drives it to the point boundary.

inn2.comm: good delivery on a good length on the middle, curving away slightly, Tamim gets the bat in front of the pad to stab it to the off side
in the zone outside off stump, leaving Tamim, who shoulders arms
outswinger outside off and Tamim tries to go after the width but doesn't quite lean into the attempt. And is beaten
lovely whippy shot. It was the full delivery on the middle, looking for the lbw, but Tamim arrested the front-foot movement and wristed it stylishly through midwicket
leans forward to defend the length delivery tailing away from him
Six over third man! It was a shortish delivery outside off and Tamim cleared the sink. Big slash. The ball flew over the very wide third man fielder who back-pedaled and jumped but in vain.
wide outside off stump and Keyes tries to reach it
Hammered! good signs so far. It was the length delivery and width on offer too and Imrul flays it over extra cover
straighter and driven back to Hastings who threatens to throw it back
beaten! it was the good-length delivery this time and that had Imrul Kayes in trouble. he went for the on-the-up shot but didn't connect
rushes down the track, looking for the big hit, and is beaten. Hmmm
leans forward to push-drive this good-length delivery to mid-off
Wild slog attempted! He took couple of steps down the track and went for a huge swing . No luck. The keeper collects
goes for the yorker, not quite at the blockhole. on the leg stump line and it hits Tamim on the pad
Supah drive! A length delivery outside off stump and Tamim crashes it through extra cover.
on the middle stump line, full in length, dabbed to midwicket for a single
the lifting delivery outside off and the batsman lets it go through to the keeper
Fat lucky inside edge! He went for the big slog over mid-on and the ball ran away to the fine-leg boundary. Mitch lets out a cry of agony
Kayes wrists this past square-leg
Wonderfully fierce cut! It was the shortish delivery outside off and Tamim has unfurled a lovely square-cut
full and in the channel outside off, Tamim tries to dispatch it to his hometown Chittagong but misses
gets forward and across this time to steer it to point
Thump-o-rama continues! Tamim gets on the front foot and scythes through the line, up and over mid-off
slower one, on the middle and leg, turned past square-leg
gets forward to drive crisply but straight to extra cover
The violence continues unabated. Short and wide and Tamim flays it through point.
not a bad delivery actually, full and on the middle, looking for the lbw, but Tamim gets forward in a hurry and lifted it neatly over short midwicket.
Silence. Screaming yorker - full delivery actually, short of the blockhole - on the middle stump line and Tamim tries to get down the bat in a hurry. Too late. Clatter!
length delivery on the middle, jabbed away to the leg side
gets forward to push it to cover
fullish, skidding away outside off, edged away to backward point
leans forward to defend this to the off side
Slower one, full and on the middle, Kayes waits and plays the pick-up shot over square-leg
leans forward to defend
leans forward to push this quietly to the off side
still from round the stumps, on the middle and leg, worked wide of mid-on where Pattinson makes a fine diving stop
tries a slower one outside off, on a length, hit uppishly but short of mid-off
leans forward to defend the length delivery to the off side
almost through him! It was a length delivery skidding towards middle and off and the batsman played outside the line and edged it to the leg side
on the off stump line, pushed away to point
full pitched delivery on the legs, flicked away for a single
Kayes breaks free with a cut shot. Width on offer and he lashed it over backward point
fullish delivery on the middle, worked through midwicket for couple of runs
a good-length delivery coming in from round the stumps, dabbed to the leg side
moves forward to drive to mid-off
on the pads, tucked around the corner for couple of runs
homing in on the off and middle, pushed out to cover
runs this down to third man for a single
slower one, on the off and middle, pushed down to the on side of the pitch
leans forward to work it to wide mid-on region for a single
on the pads, clipped to deep square-leg region
leans forward to on drive to mid-on
on the middle stump line, worked away through midwicket for two runs
fullish, on the off stump line, dug out to the off side
collects a boundary with a flick shot. Overpitched on legs and Kayes gets his wrists working over time to put that one to square-leg boundary
from round the stumps, slower cutter on the off, run down to third man for a single
Lovely straight drive. He leaned forward to caress the full delivery past his partner at the other end
Touch of class in this. length delivery outside off stump and Kayes got forward and across and played a sweet punchy shot through cover point
the bouncer this time and Kayes hops to ride the bounce and taps it down in front of him
gets forward to defend this back down the track
extra bounce on this short delivery outside off, Kayes was cramped for room and  beaten by that bounce, and ends up stabbing at thin air
in the zone outside of f stump, doesn't connect on his waft
dabs this to right of backward point for a single
bouncy delivery coming in from round the stumps, pushed out to point
full delivery outside off stump, steered to Ponting and underarms to Paine who fails to collect it. it bounced in front of him and Paine missed that! overthrows
gets back to deflect this to point. Ponting holds on to the ball this time
dabs this delivery bouncing around off stump, tapped close on the off side and they rush across
leans forward to drive to right of mid-off where Clarke intervenes with a drive
Whack! Nafees gets forward and across to thump this length delivery on the up and through covers.
slower one outside off, defended to the off side
full delivery on the off, from round the stumps, pushed back to Watto
really full delivery, pushed out to the off. Watson has tightened up his line after that wide delivery earlier in the over
homing in on the off and middle line, full in length, defended to the off, they think about a single but decided against it
clips this through to deep midwicket for a single
runs this down to third man for a single
slips down the leg side, from round the stumps, the batsman fails to connect wit the leg glance but it runs off the thigh pad to fine-leg boundary
No slips and Kayes has steered it through the unmanned area! It was a length delivery outside off and Kayes opens the bat-face and collects a boundary. Pattinson holds his head
full in length outside off and Kayes edges his square drive down to third man
bangs this one short, it moves towards ribcage, Nafees stabs it on to his body
fullish delivery from round the stumps, pushed out to the on side
short in length on the off, steered wide of third man for couple of runs
this one drifts down the leg side and it will be a wide
on the middle stump line, deflected to midwicket
stays adjacent to the line of this delivery and guides it down to third man
slower cutter outside off, again tapped down to third man
fulller in length, on the off stump line, from round the stumps, driven to short extra cover
dabs this to midwicket.
on the pads, turned past square-leg for a single
straightens on the off stump line, from round the stumps, steered to point
on the middle and off line, defends to the off side
short in length, coming in from that angle, worked to midwicket
slightly short, pulled away to deep square-leg region
stays back to clip this to deep square-leg region
goes down on his keen to sweep it to right of square-leg where Hastings makes a  half-stop. it bounced awkwardly in front of him
